BCB330Y1-Y-20205.courseTitle: Special Project in Bioinformatics and Computational Biology
BCB330Y1-Y-20205.courseDescription: An opportunity for specialized individual research in bioinformatics and computational biology by arrangement with the course coordinator and a supervisor. Significant background in both life science and computer science courses is required. Not eligible for CR/NCR option.
BCB330Y1-Y-20205.webTimetableInstructions:
This is an online, hybrid course.
Students will work primarily on their own, but are required to meet with their supervisors at mutually convenient times throughout the term.
To enrol in this course, please send an email with your student ID to m.casco@utoronto.ca

BCB430Y1-Y-20205.courseTitle: Advanced Special Project in Bioinformatics and Computational Biology
BCB430Y1-Y-20205.courseDescription: An opportunity for advanced specialized individual research in bioinformatics and computational biology by arrangement with the course coordinator and a supervisor. Significant background in both life science and computer science courses is required. BCB330Y1 is a recommended preparation for this course however students should not normally conduct their project in the same laboratory or continue their previous project. Not eligible for CR/NCR option.
BCB430Y1-Y-20205.webTimetableInstructions:
This is an online, hybrid course.  Students will work primarily on their own, but are required to meet with their supervisors at mutually convenient times throughout the term.
To enrol in this course, please send an email with your student ID to m.casco@utoronto.ca
